Dodged a bullet there

commentary: Samuels to Taylor, OUT Brendan, looking to paddle this through fine leg, ends up top-edging a chance to Ramdin, with the WI celebrating. The umpire, though, doesn't appear moved, but Ramdin and Marlon want this reviewed. Brendan didn't seem too perturbed though, and why not since replays show that this indeed went off the forearm, and not glove. But hang on, this has been given out, and I am a bit shocked as there didn't seem to be clear evidence there for this to be given out conclusively.. but the decision has come down. Brendan has to go after his fine 37
